  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>BlueStar in LA — independent family-owned + commercial-heritage platform</h2>
    <p>BlueStar's independence and commercial-heritage engineering shape the service profile more than most buyers realize. Open-burner design (Nova Burner on RNB variants, with sealed-burner RCS alternatives) is carried over from the company's commercial-stove platform — the 25,000 BTU output spec is commercial-grade in a residential chassis. For households that want commercial cooking performance in a residential stove, BlueStar delivers it more literally than most luxury competitors. The trade-off is service-maintenance cadence: open burners need more regular air-port cleaning than sealed burners, and the 25k Nova Burner draws more gas through the burner-head than a 20k sealed burner, so orifice + regulator service is more critical.</p>
    <p>Our LA BlueStar service geography concentrates where 25k output + color flexibility + PA-factory provenance matter. Bel Air + Beverly Hills ultra-luxury custom kitchens installing 60" Platinum Series with salamander broiler + French top; Hancock Park + Larchmont heritage remodels with custom color-matched Platinum; Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes chef-owned coastal households; Silver Lake + Los Feliz design-district kitchens with 750-color flexibility; Pasadena + San Marino established-luxury installs. Precious Metal trim (24k gold-plated, chrome-plated) shows up in specific ultra-luxury contexts where the stove is a visual centerpiece. Service approach respects finish integrity — we mask and cover trim during work near exterior panels, and we source matched parts through Prizer-Painter factory channels when exterior components need replacement.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>BlueStar stove failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>25k Nova Burner output reduction — orifice + air port + regulator</h3><p>Most common BlueStar service. Open-burner design susceptible to spillage carbon on air ports. Air port clean $180–$280 per burner; orifice swap $180–$280 per burner on LP/NG mismatch; regulator $220–$360.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>IR broiler uneven heat — ceramic tile + ignition</h3><p>BlueStar infrared broiler signature. Ceramic IR tile fracture under cycling; tile replacement $280–$460. IR ignition module $280–$400.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Nova Burner assembly replacement</h3><p>When burner-head geometry is damaged beyond cleaning. Full assembly $480–$720. Parts through Prizer-Painter aftermarket 5-10 days.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven igniter glow-but-no-heat</h3><p>Igniter resistance out-of-spec. Swap $260–$400 on BlueStar pro-range oven-side.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Salamander broiler (60" Platinum)</h3><p>Element service $400–$640; gas valve $360–$520. Specialty parts 7-14 day lead.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Spark-module ignition on Nova Burners</h3><p>BlueStar spark module at 7-10 year service. Swap $280–$400. Ignitor tip $200–$300.</p></div>
  </div></section>

