  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>BlueStar vs Viking vs Wolf — independent vs corporate luxury</h2>
    <p>Three luxury-category positions, distinct ownership structures.</p>
    <p><b>BlueStar (this page)</b> — Prizer-Painter family-owned Blandon PA since 1880. Hand-built US. 25k Nova Burner open-burner commercial-heritage. 750+ color program. Independent family ownership preserves product-decision continuity.</p>
    <p><b>Viking</b> — Middleby Corporation since 2002, Greenwood MS US-manufactured, 23k ProFlow sealed-burner, 20+ Brilliance color program. Corporate foodservice portfolio. See <a href="/brands/viking-stove-repair/">Viking stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p><b>Wolf</b> — Sub-Zero Group Madison WI (still independent family-owned at Sub-Zero level), 20k sealed dual-stacked, coordinated Sub-Zero/Wolf/Cove suite. See <a href="/brands/wolf-stove-repair/">Wolf stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p>Choice drivers: BlueStar for independent family + commercial-heritage open-burner + widest color program; Viking for Middleby scale + signature 23k output + US-regional parts; Wolf for Sub-Zero suite integration + Dual Fuel + established residential-luxury positioning. See also <a href="/brands/thermador-stove-repair/">Thermador stove repair</a> for BSH alternative.</p>
